      <section eId="sec_43_40_15">
        <num>43-40-15</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1925, p. 325, § 1; Ga. L. 1931, p. 231, § 1; Code 1933, § 84-1409; Ga. L. 1943, p. 572, § 1; Ga. L. 1949, p. 943, § 3; Ga. L. 1950, p. 278, § 2; Ga. L. 1965, p. 629, § 5; Ga. L. 1968, p. 277, § 2; Code 1933, § 84-1410, enacted by Ga. L. 1973, p. 100, § 1; Ga. L. 1978, p. 231, § 2; Ga. L. 1981, p. 1311, § 3; Ga. L. 1983, p. 1411, § 2; Ga. L. 1984, p. 844, § 5; Ga. L. 1986, p. 364, §§ 4, 5, 6; Ga. L. 1989, p. 1619, § 5; Ga. L. 1990, p. 8, § 43; Ga. L. 1990, p. 650, § 4; Ga. L. 1991, p. 94, § 43; Ga. L. 1991, p. 642, §§ 4, 5; Ga. L. 1993, p. 123, § 54; Ga. L. 1994, p. 1168, § 2; Ga. L. 1995, p. 1216, § 6; Ga. L. 1996, p. 6, § 43; Ga. L. 1996, p. 194, § 8; Ga. L. 1996, p. 453, § 15; Ga. L. 1998, p. 1094, § 12; Ga. L. 2000, p. 1527, § 16; Ga. L. 2003, p. 370, § 11; Ga. L. 2007, p. 483, § 7/SB 114; Ga. L. 2008, p. 324, § 43/SB 455; Ga. L. 2012, p. 1099, § 9/SB 365; Ga. L. 2017, p. 125, § 2/HB 39; Ga. L. 2019, p. 462, § 1-18/SB 214.)</p>
          <p>The 2019 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2019, in subsection (l), rewrote the first sentence, which read: "Where an applicant or licensee has been found to be a borrower in default who is not in satisfactory repayment status as provided in Code Section 20-3-295, such status shall be sufficient grounds for refusal of a license or suspension of a license.", and deleted the last sentence, which read: "In such cases, the hearing and appeal procedures provided for in Code Section 20-3-295 shall be the only such procedures required under this chapter."</p>
